import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['precipitation', 'location'])
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="location", y="precipitation", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set(xlabel='Location', ylabel='Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, ax=ax, label='Maximum Temperature')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, ax=ax, label='Minimum Temperature')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].str.capitalize()
    weather_count = data['weather'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=weather_count.index, y=weather_count.values, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    for i, v in enumerate(weather_count.values):
        plt.text(i, v, str(v), ha='center', va='bottom', fontweight='bold')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
